title: For Trade:  REMINGTON 700 LONG GUN W/ FREE FLOATING BULL BARREL
postcontent: I have a Remington 700 chambered in 30-06 Springfield. It has a couple of after market modifications done to it. It has a brand new free floating E.R. Shaw Bull Barrel with a 1/10 Right Hand twist. When ER Shaw installed the barrel they also Trued it to the receiver meaning that the barrel/chamber now sits perfectly in the receiver and lines up perfectly with the bolt face. I have put the barrel through the initial break in of firing one round then cleaning the barrel with Hoppes solvent repeating the process for 10 rounds. Also the rifle comes with a H-S Precision kevlar composite M24A1 stock that is equipped with an aluminum bedding block. The scope is nothing special. It is simply a cheap no name scope that I picked up from Gander Mountain. It also comes with the Bipod but not the sling. This rifle will stack rounds through one ragged hole at 100 meters. However, I have not had an opportunity to push it out there on the range. That being said I would not be surprised if this rifle is capable of hitting a 1 minute target at 600-800 meters, and I am pretty confident that it can be done with this weapon in the hands of a capable shooter. Slap some good glass on this bad boy and maybe an aftermarket trigger and you have a true sniper rifle chambered in 30-06. With all of that being said, I by no means have to get rid of this rifle; I just really want to see what else is out there. Please no low ball or crap offers. The barrel job and stock on this rifle alone are worth $900 in their current, like new condition. If you'd like to make an offer, I'd be interested in pretty much all firearms, especially pistols, AR's, and other long guns. I can be reached by phone call or text at REDACTED ask for Jake. title: For Sale:  Eberlestock EBR Stealth Sniper Rifle Chassis w/ Folding Stock Remington 700LA
postcontent:
ntroducing the Eberlestock Model 11 Stealth Rifle Chassis system.  This premium, state-of-the-art rifle stock is designed to get maximum performance out of both rifle and marksman. It takes full advantage of modern engineering, design, and manufacturing technologies, resulting in a level of precision that nears perfection. 

We believe that the rifle stock is one of the most important components of a firearm.  A stock with the right geometry, the right ergonomics, and precisely made parts in the right places, combined with a good quality commercial-off-the-shelf rifle, can give exceptional performance.  Given the level of quality and reliability that are found in the rifles produced by today's firearms industry, you don't need to spend thousands of dollars on a custom rig in order to obtain a highly accurate precision rifle.  Our test rifles are all over-the-counter guns, and when shot with factory loads out of the Stealth Chassis they all shoot half-minute groups.  We don't attribute all of this performance to the Stealth Chassis system, but we certainly have taken a good measure of error out of the equation.  So, now you have the four main components of an accurate firearm readily available to you: quality commercial rifles, premium optics, excellent factory load ammunition, linked to the marksman with the fourth component, the Stealth Chassis.  We believe that the Model 11 provides you with the perfect man-to-machine interface.  And of course, it needn't be said that this chassis is also meant to bring a custom rifle up to its full level of capability.

We make no apology that this chassis is not for everyone.  Simply put, it is what it was meant to be; it is simple yet sophisticated.  Cut out of billets of aluminum, we achieve great accuracy through a considerable amount of time spent by each and every part on state-of-the-art milling machines, cut to exacting tolerances.  Materials and components are appropriately chosen for their role in the overall structure, and all aluminum parts are finished in hard anodized field colors.  So we invite you to compare this to a fine sports car, or to a high-end optic.  Study the number of parts and their level of refinement, and you will see that the Stealth is offered at a fair price and provides a good value.

title: For Sale:  For Sale: Eberlestock EBR Stealth Sniper Rifle Chassis w/ Folding Stock Remington 700LA
postcontent:
ntroducing the Eberlestock Model 11 Stealth Rifle Chassis system. This premium, state-of-the-art rifle stock is designed to get maximum performance out of both rifle and marksman. It takes full advantage of modern engineering, design, and manufacturing technologies, resulting in a level of precision that nears perfection.

We believe that the rifle stock is one of the most important components of a firearm. A stock with the right geometry, the right ergonomics, and precisely made parts in the right places, combined with a good quality commercial-off-the-shelf rifle, can give exceptional performance. Given the level of quality and reliability that are found in the rifles produced by today's firearms industry, you don't need to spend thousands of dollars on a custom rig in order to obtain a highly accurate precision rifle. Our test rifles are all over-the-counter guns, and when shot with factory loads out of the Stealth Chassis they all shoot half-minute groups. We don't attribute all of this performance to the Stealth Chassis system, but we certainly have taken a good measure of error out of the equation. So, now you have the four main components of an accurate firearm readily available to you: quality commercial rifles, premium optics, excellent factory load ammunition, linked to the marksman with the fourth component, the Stealth Chassis. We believe that the Model 11 provides you with the perfect man-to-machine interface. And of course, it needn't be said that this chassis is also meant to bring a custom rifle up to its full level of capability.

We make no apology that this chassis is not for everyone. Simply put, it is what it was meant to be; it is simple yet sophisticated. Cut out of billets of aluminum, we achieve great accuracy through a considerable amount of time spent by each and every part on state-of-the-art milling machines, cut to exacting tolerances. Materials and components are appropriately chosen for their role in the overall structure, and all aluminum parts are finished in hard anodized field colors. So we invite you to compare this to a fine sports car, or to a high-end optic. Study the number of parts and their level of refinement, and you will see that the Stealth is offered at a fair price and provides a good value.

Our focus is on simplicity, reliability, and accuracy, with just the right features to give you a versatile platform and an excellent interface with your rifle. Eberlestock has been at work on this project since the early 2000's, when we developed one of the industry's first modular chassis systems. We now think that its time has come.
